        "text": "@Masechaba Khoza Please prioritize this one from your side , ideally added to the up coming sprint. \n\nI have just received the correspondence below indicating that there's an impending fine coming UCOOKs way again. Although this project wont mitigate the need for us to pay the fine it should mitigate any future fines incurred. \n\ncc @Anton Geyer @Andrew W @Danel Botha @Paul Robinson \nWe received two notifications from Scheme and Nedbank about some non compliance issues. The first one is related to Ucook where Scheme notified us about the use of failed RG to process subsequent transactions. Could you please liaise with the Ucook development team asking them to review the integration to ensure no failed RG are stored for future use. Note that in the live environment, only when a pre-authorisation or debits returns the response code 000.000.000 should the token (RG) be considered as successful and stored to process subsequent payments."
